{
  "texts": [
    "multiple Outcome instances, can be created from these slot fillers.",
    "Deciding which slot fillers belong together is however not a trivial task.The assignment of extracted SFs to template instances is therefore done in ITC by a clustering approach per template based on a pairwise similarity or compatibility function q: R d × R d → [0, 1].",
    "q scores the similarity between two SFs in the sense that they belong to the same template instance, where g(e i, e j) = 1 indicates maxi- mum similarity such that e i and e j should be assigned to the same template instance.",
    "Note that e i and e j are entity representations calculated based on the contextualized embeddings generated by the used models.",
    "Thus, we can use results from the established field of (density-based) clustering to figure out the SF grouping."
  ]
}